f=Cybersecurity/veil/operational/tool/veil-tool-requirements.md · h1:veil — Tool Requirements=**Specifies needs; grant them.** Access configured deployment (Fleet Charter Rails 1–2). external call plan-locked sandboxed. · h1:veil — Tool Requirements=\| Skill \| Needs \| Why \| · h1:veil — Tool Requirements=\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:veil — Tool Requirements=\| data-classification \| File read/write; classification policy reference \| Define and apply classification tiers \| · h1:veil — Tool Requirements=\| privacy-by-design \| File read/write; regulatory text references (GDPR, etc.) \| DPIA documentation, compliance review \| · h1:veil — Tool Requirements=\| data-loss-prevention \| DLP tool read access (alerts, logs, policy); file read/write \| DLP alert review, policy tuning \| · h1:veil — Tool Requirements=\| breach-notification \| File read/write; notification contact access (email/portal) \| Draft notifications, track deadlines \| · h2:Explicit non-needs hard prohibition (the security-inversion)=**NO execute access DLP enforcement** (block egress, quarantine files, restrict user). veil identifies violations; operator enforces blocks., **NO send authority notifications.** veil drafts; operator legal counsel approves sends., **NO write access production data stores** veil reads classification metadata DLP alerts; modify data. · n=veil sees what data exists it's going; cannot stop notify about unilaterally., DLP read access important technical dependency; without it, egress monitoring manual.